on and anti-witchcraft texts from Ras Shamra as a unified corpus. These texts, dealing with impending dangers (mainly snakebites) and witchcraft attacks, are placed in the context of Ancient Near Eastern magic literature. A discussion of general topics, including magic and religion, the Ugaritic gods of magic, and the definition of incantation, is followed by a new collation and translation of the Akkadian texts, as well as new photographic material for both series. The main focus of this book is the close reading of the consonantal texts in the context of the much larger and better analyzed corpus of Akkadian magic literature.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aMagic. 4aSnakebite. 4aUgarit. 4aWitchcraft. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aMagic.  aUgaritic.  asnakebite.  awitchcraft.1 aMárquez Rowe, Ignacio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRowe, Ignacio Márquez, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA History 2000 - 2014z9783110635836oZDB-23-GHI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2014z9783110369618oZDB-23-DGD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG0 cEPUBz97816145190340 cprintz978161451627940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978161451492340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781614514923423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781614514923/original  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  a